# Frontend (Next.js + TypeScript)

The dashboard is **read-only**. It never places orders, never holds API
keys, and never talks to an exchange.

## Required

- App Router (Next.js 14). Server components by default; mark client
  islands with `"use client"` only when needed (charts, tables, forms).
- All API calls go through `frontend/lib/api.ts`. No raw `fetch` in components.
- `tsconfig.strict: true`. CI runs `npm run typecheck`.
- File naming: `kebab-case.tsx` for files, `PascalCase` for components.
- Numeric cells render through `formatNumber` / `formatPct` / `formatDate`
  in `frontend/lib/utils.ts`. Numbers are right-aligned and monospace.

## Visual rules

- Dark theme by default (`html.dark`). Brand color: `hsl(160 84% 50%)`.
- Charts use **TradingView Lightweight Charts only** (no Chart.js, no D3).
- Tables use **TanStack Table**. Sortable defaults must be explicit so
  reloads are stable.
- Status colors: live = primary; paper = warning; retired = danger.

## Forbidden

- Order-placement UI. Trade controls live in the trading engine.
- Embedding API keys, tokens, or secrets in client code.
- Surfacing LLM responses as actionable trading signals.
- Importing from any `backend/` Python module (frontend is its own app).

## Tests

A new page must boot in the standalone Next image used by CI. See
[`docker.mdc`](mdc:.cursor/rules/docker.mdc).
